6static int
7mechanisms_wrap(int argc, char **argv)
8{
9 int ret;
10 int optidx = 0;
11 struct getargs args[] = {
12 { "help", 'h', arg_flag, NULL, NULL, NULL }
13 };
14 int help_flag = 0;
15 args[0].value = &help_flag;
16 if(getarg(args, 1, argc, argv, &optidx))
17 goto usage;
18 if(argc - optidx > 0) {
19 fprintf(stderr, "Arguments given (%u) are more than expected (0).\n\n", argc - optidx);
20 goto usage;
21 }
22 if(help_flag)
23 goto usage;
24 ret = mechanisms(NULL, argc - optidx, argv + optidx);
25 return ret;
26usage:
27 arg_printusage (args, 1, "mechanisms", "");
28 return 0;
29}

31static int
32attributes_wrap(int argc, char **argv)
33{
34 struct attributes_options opt;
35 int ret;
36 int optidx = 0;
37 struct getargs args[] = {
38 { "all", 0, arg_flag, NULL, NULL, NULL },
39 { "mech", 0, arg_string, NULL, NULL, "mechanism" },
40 { "help", 'h', arg_flag, NULL, NULL, NULL }
41 };
42 int help_flag = 0;
43 opt.all_flag = 0;
44 opt.mech_string = NULL;
45 args[0].value = &opt.all_flag;
46 args[1].value = &opt.mech_string;
47 args[2].value = &help_flag;
48 if(getarg(args, 3, argc, argv, &optidx))
49 goto usage;
50 if(help_flag)
51 goto usage;
52 ret = attributes(&opt, argc - optidx, argv + optidx);
53 return ret;
54usage:
55 arg_printusage (args, 3, "attributes", "");
56 return 0;
57}
58
59static int
60help_wrap(int argc, char **argv)
61{
62 int ret;
63 int optidx = 0;
64 struct getargs args[] = {
65 { "help", 'h', arg_flag, NULL, NULL, NULL }
66 };
67 int help_flag = 0;
68 args[0].value = &help_flag;
69 if(getarg(args, 1, argc, argv, &optidx))
70 goto usage;
71 if(argc - optidx > 1) {
72 fprintf(stderr, "Arguments given (%u) are more than expected (1).\n\n", argc - optidx);
73 goto usage;
74 }
75 if(argc - optidx < 0) {
76 fprintf(stderr, "Arguments given (%u) are less than expected (0).\n\n", argc - optidx);
77 goto usage;
78 }
79 if(help_flag)
80 goto usage;
81 ret = help(NULL, argc - optidx, argv + optidx);
82 return ret;
83usage:
84 arg_printusage (args, 1, "help", "[command]");
85 return 0;
86}
